Here you can see the operator precedence https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/operator_precedence

The statement 

    abc = abc + abc + abc = abc +2;

is equivalent to

    abc + abc + abc = abc +2;
    abc = abc + abc + abc;

The first line 

    abc + abc + abc = abc +2;

is not valid because the expression

    abc + abc + abc

is an rvalue. You can&#39;t assign a value to it.

